add options to libsvn_diff to ignore whitespace and eol style.

author: blair
msg: Fix the svnmerge.py test suite to work with the version of svnmerge.py
in svn.collab.net.
* contrib/client-side/test_svnmerge.py:
Remove the svn:keywords property, as they mess with the
TestCase_kwextract.test_basic and the
TestCase_kwextract.test_failure tests which expect a specific
value of $Rev$ and $Date$.
(TestCase_TestRepo.testCommitFileDisabled):
Remove this test since the svnmerge.py in svn.collab.net will not
prevent generation of the commit log message file with the -f-
command line option.  This behavior is enabled in Giovanni Bajo's
repository, but was not accepted by the community, since -f-
commonly means, send the output to standard output.

author: blair
msg: Copy over svnmerge.py's test suite from Giovanni Bajo's Subversion
repository that used to be the canonical repository for svnmerge.py.
This test suite does fail on the 'testCommitFileDisabled
(__main__.TestCase_TestRepo)' test, but I want to copy the file over
unmodified.  The next commit will fix this.
* contrib/client-side/test_svnmerge.py:
New file copied unmodified from revision 236 of
svn://pyinstaller.hpcf.upr.edu/svnmerge/test_svnmerge.py .
There are newer revisions of this file in the other repository, but
those contain changes not ready to be merged into svn.collab.net.
